Taita Taveta governor Granton Samboja has launched a competitive livestock auctioning ceremony at Bachuma in a bid to boost livestock production in the county. He said the county governmentÂ  will promote livestock breeding for improvement and profitability of their products. "We are doing this with a view of making livestock farmers to start exporting their products to European Union and Asian markets," he said on Tuesday. The mational government is funding the construction of a Sh2.6 billion world-class livestock export zone. It will be constructed at Bachuma LMD as part of efforts to encourage farmers in Kenya gain access to international livestock market. The project is being executed under the Disease Free Zone initiative. Agriculture CEC Davis Mwangoma challenged livestock farmers to tap the opportunity and keep high quality breeds. "The county administration is ready to offer maximum support," he said. Click here for the latest political news